caption: Friends took me here while I was visiting just before Covid in 2020. I was pleasantly surprised by the menu. The drinks were great, and the food was both beautiful and delicious.
The sort of neighborhood bar you dream about. The mixed drinks are especially terrific.
Kitchen staff are the backbone of this place, keep up the great work. Great location as well.

Really good food at good prices for the portion. Their bar food is yum, their thai is pretty authentic compared to others locally and delicious. Love the veggie pickles and the curries and chicken sandwich! Eating in pre covid was fun and lively but now we do delivery, order directly from their website for the best prices and good service.
Lovely one

The sweet potato fries with maple glaze are a must. They are delicious! The vegan and nonvegan sausages are tasty. Good assortment of beers and several beer flights available too. Small bar and it gets packed quickly.
Roti with Chicken curry is delicious
Why would you continue to accept online orders and when the delivery driver attempts to pick up, you are completely AWOL? Ridiculous.

The Expat is a great pub to go for after work.  They have a super nice place, that gives a nice vibe of an Irish pub with Asian influences.  They have a variety of unique cocktails which you should try. Otherwise they offer a good beer selection. When I went there they had 4 beers on tap and several bottles.  The food is amazing! We started with the cauliflower wings and tofu appetizer. The sauce of both dishes is delicious,you have to try it.  The entre was the beyond meat burger. Great made with a lot of fries. You will definitely be satisfied.  The dessert was the lava cake. Amazing! A great Finale for a wonderful time.  The service was all the time great. All people are friendly and ensure that you have a great time.  When you have the chance, go here it is a great experience!
Hidden gem but trust me, food is very good, you need to try Thai Ginger Chicken noodle soup its sooooo good.
Good asian fusion food. Friendly staff. The prices were a little high, but beer was great.
Quality cocktails, bar and dining experience. Also great hosting smaller gatherings, 10-15 max.

Truly outstanding food! So happy to have this place just around the corner from Columbia...they have plenty of outside sitting currently which is super nice. The server was so nice and knowledgeable and recommended just the drink that I needed :-) Will be visiting more often once the university fully reopens!
Top notch service and food. Couldn’t recommend more highly.  Literally everything we ordered was fantastic.
Love this place! Such tasty food and amazing service! My go-to restaurant for sure!

Wish I had known about this place pre covid.. we got a peak of the interior and love the retro vibe. Clueless was playing in a projector in the back. Currently have open outdoor seating on both sides of the corner block. Staff was super sweet and let us use the bathroom.
Curry chicken really good, but a little salty. They are using disposable utensils and containers in reopening NYC phase during COVID-19

Everything on the menu is so good. Too recommendations are:  1) Chicken and mochi waffles - chicken was cooked perfectly and seasoned well. The waffles might be the best I've ever tasted  2) vegatarian Singaporean street noodles - definitely very Americanized, but I liked how the tofu was minced and not over powering.
Perfect place for a weekday evening hangout! I love their Bangkok Mule and their small bites. They swap the wings for  cauliflower, to make amazing vegetarian options!
Without a doubt the best neighborhood bar you could ask for
Super fast delivery, and good food. Everything tasted fresh and good quality. Will definitely order here again.
Good food and great service during pandemic. The tofu bites and cauliflower wings are amazing

Wish I would have found out about this place sooner, but have ordered food from them twice so far. Everything has been so delicious! And they also have sake juice boxes, how could you not love it. Will definitely be visiting this place in person when I can.

I'm rooting for this place based on proximity, styling, friendliness of the staff and drink quality. Really enjoyed the prosecco and cocktails I've had so far at The Expat.  But, the food menu. Welllll, I'd hold out a while until the full menu is presented and the kinks worked out. The Caesar salad is overpriced for some iceberg lettuce. The shrimp dumplings were passable. The pork sliders were satisfying on an unexpectedly tasty and function English muffin.  Update: many moons later the menu has expanded and been refined. It's delicious. The pork nachos -- all day, every day. That poor lettuce wedge still exists tho.

Amazing food unlike any restaurant in the area! Super fast delivery and  I was so impressed with the precautions taken by the delivery staff- always with gloves, mask and happy to leave at the doorstep.  Thanks Expat!!
A great spot to meet friends. Drinks are a little overpriced to be honest, but the spot is cool. The food is surprisingly great!
Favorite spot in the neighborhood! Good food, good drinks, good vibes!

Delicious food, GREAT drinks, and a super welcoming atmosphere. I almost don’t want you to know about this place, but it’s SO GOOD! Come on down, let me known when you want to grab a drink, can’t wait to go again.

It's not your typical vietnamese restaurant.  It had a lot of interesting decor. But i lt was a warm environment.  It got a little loud towards the end with the locals. But the food was excellent. I had the yellow curry chicken which was flavorful and not spicy.

This was my first time ordering from this restaurant. I can’t speak for the deco, service, or ambience but the food was horrible. I ordered a simple basil chicken fried rice and the firecracker wings which claimed to be spicy sweet and sour. Well the food wasn’t warm, the fried rice was soggy and tasted bland. The chicken wings were just your regular bbq wings that you could get for $5 (if I am going by taste and presentation) at any bbq fast food. Let’s just  say, next time  I’ll be taking that $34 dollars spent to my local restaurant where I can get the same for $20 (without the soggy rice and bland tasteless bbq wings).
This place is great. Truly adapts the idea of an expatriate in an international country.  The food is flavourful and authentic.  Definitely try the Yellow Curry, and get it spicy.  Service was great.

Went for happy hour and really enjoyed it. The drink specials are worth it, $5 house beer and cocktail among others, and cheap appetizers. I'll definitely be going back both for the food and the service which was attentive but from a distance which was perfect.
Really good food and ambiance

Wow. Hidden gem off the beaten path. We've been here a few times. First when it had just opened for drinks. Craft cocktails done very well, and very consistent. There is a cocktail for everyone it seems.  Food was great too. The nachos weren't typical. We also had the Singapore noodles and beef curry. Curry was amazing as was the noddles as recommended by the bar.  Service was great too. Bartenders friendly and make you feel very welcome.  Definitely adding this place into the regular rotation.
Great Love the ambience

Stopped in to try the restaurant around 9:30 pm. There weren’t any tables available nor at the bar.  We were happy to wait but were not even offered an opportunity to put our name on the dinner waitlist but were just turned away. Disappointed.
The food and drinks are excellent, as was the service. We all loved our entrees and the firecracker wings were perfect ♥  Edit: sorry for the original 1 star review, it was a slip of the finger.

Great atmosphere. I love how the bar is right below street level. It means that inside the windows are just a bit elevated from your table, which has a well like feel. The staff was helpful, although they mixed up our tabs. All in all I like the bar and will come back. It's conveniently located a few minutes away from the 125th St 1 train stop.
Great atmosphere, drinks and food! Great selection of Sake too!
Great ambience with interesting cocktails and food. Awesome happy hour! Will def be a regular.
Amazing food and very friendly place for a first date and a good time with friends! Would recommend to anyone in NYC! 👌
Amazing decor, friendly staff, authentic Southern Asia food with very reasonable price. A great addition to the neighbourhood.
Love the atmosphere and drinks!

This is the very first time that I’m writing a review for anything, but this is a must. First, I personally would like to have a conversation with whoever thought that putting a BAR in a RESIDENTIAL neighborhood is a good idea. Claremont Avenue was a relatively quiet and peaceful place to live in. Notice that I use WAS. This bar has changed everything. Whenever I open the window at night, all I hear is noise and music playing way too loud than it should. I understand that I live in nyc and I should expect noise, but Claremont Avenue is a residential neighborhood and secluded from broadway. And it’s not like we don’t have enough bars in the area. There’s two across the street! And all I hear while I’m trying to sleep is drunk people talking loudly as they leave the bar. Ever since the bar came, I repeatedly hear fights and presumably drunk people coming out of the bar fighting and cursing at each other. How disrespectful, inappropriate, and rude that is when you take the elderly and young children living in the area into account. I live on the fifth floor of a building in the area, but can still hear the noise. It’s disruptive when you’re trying to work and simply inconvenient and annoying. I don’t mind the bar if it keeps the noise down and if people don’t stumble out drunk and fight and curse at each other while the bar closes and I’m trying to sleep. Unfortunately fans not the way that it is and this bar needs to go! It’s a huge inconvenience and annoyance for everyone living in the neighborhood!

We sat in a roomy booth near the front door and watched all the dog walkers and families go by while we sipped our Kumquat Spritzers (a great refreshing summer vodka cocktail) and yummy Vietnamese summer rolls and Thai sausages.
